VanDyne SuperTurbo Grabs Funding to Commercialize Product
April 15, 2014



Share:




 



VanDyne SuperTurbo has received $15 million in funding. The money will go towards the commercialization of its SuperTurbo technology, which combines a turbocharger and a transmission into a single device, while addressing both cost and gas emission concerns. It plans to initially focus on several target markets including on-highway trucking, natural gas, off-highway equipment manufacturing and automotive industries. Northwater Capital Management was the lead investor in the round that also saw participation from other existing investors.






VanDyne SuperTurbo



Industrial Supplies and Parts


Loveland, CO


$15 million


Series C


